Time-Frequency Analysis Dashboard

Chirp Event Characteristics

This dashboard reveals the intricate relationships between temporal and spectral characteristics of chirp events. The main scatter plot illustrates how start frequency correlates with temporal duration, while color-coding shows end frequency patterns. The correlation matrix reveals interdependencies between time-frequency parameters.

Channel & SOZ Analysis

Anatomical Distribution and Seizure Focus Patterns

The channel analysis reveals preferential recording sites and their relationship to seizure onset zones (SOZ). This spatial analysis is critical for understanding the anatomical distribution of chirp events and their clinical significance in seizure localization and surgical planning.
